cucumber.api

Class DataTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • cucumber.api.DataTable

  • public class DataTable
extends Object
    Represents the data from a Gherkin DataTable. Cucumber will convert the table in Gherkin to a DataTable instance and pass it to a step definition.

      • asMap

        public <K,V> Map<K,V> asMap(Class<K> keyType,
                            Class<V> valueType)
        Converts the table to a single Map. The left column is used as keys, the right column as values.
        Type Parameters:
        K - key type
        V - value type
        Parameters:
        keyType - key type
        valueType - value type
        Returns:
        a Map.
        Throws:
        cucumber.runtime.CucumberException - if the table doesn't have 2 columns.

      • asList

        public <T> List<T> asList(Class<T> itemType)
        Converts the table to a List. If itemType is a scalar type the table is flattened. Otherwise, the top row is used to name the fields/properties and the remaining rows are turned into list items.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the list items
        Parameters:
        itemType - the type of the list items
        Returns:
        a List of objects
